{
    "Final_Answer": 10100,
    "Evidence_Text": "Data is extracted from the 'Summary External Debt Data' tables in the IDR 2025. Nigeria (page 203): 2020 Multilateral PPG = 14,328; 2020 Total PPG = 32,057; 2020 PPG Principal = 451; 2020 PPG Interest = 1,115; 2020 PPG Disbursements = 4,379. 2024 Multilateral PPG = 23,800; 2024 Total PPG = 50,192; 2024 PPG Principal = 1,661; 2024 PPG Interest = 2,199; 2024 PPG Disbursements = 8,495. Pakistan (page 205): 2020 Multilateral PPG = 33,339; 2020 Total PPG = 86,908; 2020 PPG Principal = 6,596; 2020 PPG Interest = 1,701; 2020 PPG Disbursements = 13,049. 2024 Multilateral PPG = 39,537; 2024 Total PPG = 89,556; 2024 PPG Principal = 7,471; 2024 PPG Interest = 3,745; 2024 PPG Disbursements = 5,246. All figures are in US$ millions.",
    "Derivation": "Step 1 (Nigeria 2020): Share = (14328 / 32057) * 100 = 44.70%. DSDR = (451 + 1115) / 4379 = 0.36. Step 2 (Nigeria 2024): Share = (23800 / 50192) * 100 = 47.42%. DSDR = (1661 + 2199) / 8495 = 0.45. Step 3 (Nigeria Deltas): Delta Share = |47.42 - 44.70| = 2.72. Delta DSDR = |0.45 - 0.36| = 0.09. Step 4 (Pakistan 2020): Share = (33339 / 86908) * 100 = 38.36%. DSDR = (6596 + 1701) / 13049 = 0.64. Step 5 (Pakistan 2024): Share = (39537 / 89556) * 100 = 44.15%. DSDR = (7471 + 3745) / 5246 = 2.14. Step 6 (Pakistan Deltas): Delta Share = |44.15 - 38.36| = 5.79. Delta DSDR = |2.14 - 0.64| = 1.50. Step 7 (Global Index): 2.72 + 0.09 + 5.79 + 1.50 = 10.10. Step 8: 10.10 * 1000 = 10100.",
    "Reference": [
      ["International Debt Report 2025.pdf", 203],
      ["International Debt Report 2025.pdf", 205]
    ]
  }

